'''Maryellen O'Shaughnessy''' is a [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] politician from [[Columbus, Ohio]] and current Franklin County Clerk of Courts, now serving in her third consecutive term.

==Background==
O'Shaughnessy is a fifth-generation [[Columbus, Ohio metropolitan area|Central Ohioan]].{{sfn|Clerk of Courts}}{{sfn|Franklin County Democratic Party}} She graduated from [[Bishop Watterson High School]] and received a B.A. from The [[Ohio State University]] in Journalism.{{sfn|Franklin County Democratic Party}}

O'Shaughnessy is a fourth-generation funeral director and owner of the O'Shaughnessy Company Funeral Directors, established in 1889.{{sfn|Franklin County Democratic Party}} She lost to [[Pat Tiberi]] in 2000 for [[Ohio's 12th congressional district]].{{sfn|Vote2000}} She was elected to three terms on the [[Columbus, Ohio|Columbus]] City Council before being elected to Franklin County Clerk of Courts in 2008.{{sfn|Clerk of Courts}}

In 2010, O'Shaughnessy was the Democratic Party nominee for [[Ohio Secretary of State]]. She was opposed by [[United States Republican Party|Republican]] [[Jon A. Husted]], then a member of the [[Ohio State Senate]], and previously [[List of Speakers of the Ohio House of Representatives|Speaker of the Ohio House]], and [[Libertarian Party (United States)|Libertarian]] Charles Earl. Husted won election with 53.7% to O'Shaughnessy's 41.5% and Earl's 4.8%.{{sfn|Vote2010}}

O'Shaughnessy ran unopposed for a second four-year term as Clerk of Courts in 2012.  In 2016, O'Shaughnessy was again victorious in her third election earning more than 67% of votes over her opponent.  The current term ends January, 2021.{{sfn|Franklin County Democratic Party}}

==Personal==
[[File:MEOShaugnessy 2016.jpg|left|thumbnail|O'Shaughnessy in March 2016]]
O'Shaughnessy lives in [[Columbus, Ohio]]. A member of the [[Roman Catholic Church]], she has received the Diocesan Service Award. She has served or currently is on the boards of the Columbus Historical Society and the Greenways Working Group of the Mid-Ohio Regional Planning Commission, the [[metropolitan planning organization]] for central Ohio.{{sfn|Franklin County Democratic Party}}

